The paper discusses the development of a Smart Home environment using service robots and IoT, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a learning and reasoning algorithm for the Smart Home environment, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The focus on improving human welfare through the reduction of home labor suggests a potential overlap with the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Finally, the use of IoT in the Smart Home environment suggests a potential overlap with the Internet of Things (cs.IOT) category.
